## Overview
Implement the `packages/data` package: drift SQLite schema, migrations, and concrete implementations of the three repository interfaces defined in `packages/domain`.

## Depends on
- while-youre-out-3r5 (domain package must exist with interfaces defined)

## Package location
`packages/data/`

## Key dependencies (pubspec.yaml)
```yaml
dependencies:
  domain:
    path: ../domain
  drift: ^2.18.0
  sqlite3_flutter_libs: ^0.5.0
  path_provider: ^2.1.0
  path: ^1.9.0
  uuid: ^4.0.0

dev_dependencies:
  drift_dev: ^2.18.0
  build_runner: ^2.4.0
  very_good_analysis: ^5.1.0
```

## Database schema (lib/src/database/)

### File: `app_database.dart`
Drift database class that includes all three tables:

```dart
@DriftDatabase(tables: [TodoListsTable, TodoItemsTable, GeofenceRegionsTable])
class AppDatabase extends _$AppDatabase {
  AppDatabase() : super(_openConnection());

  @override
  int get schemaVersion => 1;

  @override
  MigrationStrategy get migration => MigrationStrategy(
    onCreate: (m) => m.createAll(),
    onUpgrade: (m, from, to) async { /* future migrations here */ },
  );
}

LazyDatabase _openConnection() {
  return LazyDatabase(() async {
    final dbFolder = await getApplicationDocumentsDirectory();
    final file = File(path.join(dbFolder.path, 'while_youre_out.db'));
    // Exclude from iCloud backup
    await file.setAttributes({FileAttribute.excludedFromBackup: true}); // iOS only
    return NativeDatabase.createInBackground(file);
  });
}
```

### Drift table definitions
```dart
// TodoListsTable
class TodoListsTable extends Table {
  TextColumn get id => text()();
  TextColumn get title => text()();
  IntColumn get color => integer().withDefault(const Constant(0xFF2196F3))();
  BoolColumn get notifyOnEnter => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(true))();
  BoolColumn get notifyOnExit => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(false))();
  TextColumn get geofenceId => text().nullable()();
  IntColumn get sortOrder => integer().withDefault(const Constant(0))();
  DateTimeColumn get createdAt => dateTime()();

  @override
  Set<Column> get primaryKey => {id};
}

// TodoItemsTable
class TodoItemsTable extends Table {
  TextColumn get id => text()();
  TextColumn get listId => text().references(TodoListsTable, #id, onDelete: KeyAction.cascade)();
  TextColumn get title => text()();
  TextColumn get notes => text().nullable()();
  BoolColumn get isDone => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(false))();
  DateTimeColumn get dueDate => dateTime().nullable()();
  IntColumn get priority => integer().withDefault(const Constant(0))();

  @override
  Set<Column> get primaryKey => {id};
}

// GeofenceRegionsTable
class GeofenceRegionsTable extends Table {
  TextColumn get id => text()();
  RealColumn get latitude => real()();
  RealColumn get longitude => real()();
  RealColumn get radiusMeters => real()();
  TextColumn get label => text().withDefault(const Constant(''))();
  BoolColumn get isActive => boolean().withDefault(const Constant(true))();
  TextColumn get trigger => text().withDefault(const Constant('enter'))();  // 'enter'|'exit'|'enterAndExit'
  DateTimeColumn get createdAt => dateTime()();

  @override
  Set<Column> get primaryKey => {id};
}
```
Add index: CREATE INDEX todo_item_list_done ON todo_items_table(list_id, is_done).

## Repository implementations (lib/src/repositories/)

### `DriftTodoListRepository` implements `TodoListRepository`
- `getAllLists()`: SELECT all, ORDER BY sort_order ASC
- `watchAllLists()`: use drift `watch()` query
- `getListById(String id)`: SELECT WHERE id = ?
- `saveList(TodoList list)`: drift `insertOnConflictUpdate`
- `deleteList(String id)`: DELETE WHERE id = ?

### `DriftTodoItemRepository` implements `TodoItemRepository`
- `getItemsForList(String listId)`: SELECT WHERE list_id = ?, ORDER BY priority DESC, is_done ASC
- `watchItemsForList(String listId)`: drift `watch()`
- `saveItem(TodoItem item)`: `insertOnConflictUpdate`
- `deleteItem(String id)`: DELETE WHERE id = ?
- `countIncompleteItems(String listId)`: SELECT COUNT(*) WHERE list_id = ? AND is_done = 0

### `DriftGeofenceRepository` implements `GeofenceRepository`
- All standard CRUD operations

## Data mappers (lib/src/mappers/)
Provide extension methods or static helper classes to convert between drift-generated row types and domain entities.

## Barrel export
`lib/data.dart` — export the `AppDatabase` and the three repository implementations.

## Tests (test/)
Use `drift` in-memory test database (`NativeDatabase.memory()`) — do NOT mock drift internals.
- Test saveList + getAllLists roundtrip
- Test deleteList cascades to todo_items
- Test watchAllLists emits when data changes
- Test countIncompleteItems correctness
- Test ON DELETE CASCADE for todo items when list deleted

## Acceptance criteria
- `melos test:data` passes with ≥90% coverage
- `melos analyze` passes on this package
- Generated drift files committed (or .gitignore updated to track them)

## Overview
Implement the `packages/domain` package: all domain entities, repository interfaces (abstractions), and use cases. This is a pure Dart package with zero external dependencies.

## Depends on
- while-youre-out-qys (monorepo scaffold must exist first)

## Package location
`packages/domain/`

## Entities (lib/src/entities/)
Create the following Dart classes (plain value objects, use `equatable` or manual `==`/`hashCode`):

```dart
// TodoList
class TodoList {
  final String id;       // UUID
  final String title;
  final int color;       // ARGB int (matches Flutter Color.value)
  final bool notifyOnEnter;
  final bool notifyOnExit;
  final String? geofenceId;  // nullable FK to GeofenceRegion
  final int sortOrder;
  final DateTime createdAt;
}

// TodoItem
class TodoItem {
  final String id;        // UUID
  final String listId;    // FK
  final String title;
  final String? notes;
  final bool isDone;
  final DateTime? dueDate;
  final int priority;     // 0=none, 1=low, 2=medium, 3=high
}

// GeofenceRegion
class GeofenceRegion {
  final String id;        // UUID
  final double latitude;
  final double longitude;
  final double radiusMeters;
  final String label;
  final bool isActive;
  final GeofenceTrigger trigger;  // enum: enter, exit, enterAndExit
  final DateTime createdAt;
}

enum GeofenceTrigger { enter, exit, enterAndExit }
```

## Repository interfaces (lib/src/repositories/)
These are abstract classes that the `data` package implements:

```dart
abstract class TodoListRepository {
  Future<List<TodoList>> getAllLists();
  Stream<List<TodoList>> watchAllLists();        // for reactive UI
  Future<TodoList?> getListById(String id);
  Future<void> saveList(TodoList list);
  Future<void> deleteList(String id);
}

abstract class TodoItemRepository {
  Future<List<TodoItem>> getItemsForList(String listId);
  Stream<List<TodoItem>> watchItemsForList(String listId);
  Future<void> saveItem(TodoItem item);
  Future<void> deleteItem(String id);
  Future<int> countIncompleteItems(String listId);  // for badge
}

abstract class GeofenceRepository {
  Future<GeofenceRegion?> getGeofenceById(String id);
  Future<List<GeofenceRegion>> getAllActiveGeofences();
  Future<void> saveGeofence(GeofenceRegion region);
  Future<void> deleteGeofence(String id);
}
```

## OS service interfaces (lib/src/services/)
Abstract classes implemented by `geofencing` and `notifications` packages:

```dart
abstract class GeofenceService {
  Future<void> registerRegion(GeofenceRegion region);
  Future<void> unregisterRegion(String regionId);
  Future<void> unregisterAll();
  Stream<GeofenceEvent> get events;  // GeofenceEvent = { regionId, type: enter|exit, timestamp }
}

abstract class NotificationService {
  Future<void> initialize();
  Future<void> postListNotification({ required String listId, required String listTitle, required int incompleteCount });
  Future<bool> requestPermission();
}
```

## Use cases (lib/src/use_cases/)
Each use case is a class with a single `call` method. Inject repository/service dependencies via constructor.

| Class | Constructor deps | call() signature | Logic |
|---|---|---|---|
| `CreateListUseCase` | TodoListRepository | `Future<TodoList> call({required String title, int color = 0xFF2196F3})` | Generate UUID, set sortOrder = max+1, save |
| `DeleteListUseCase` | TodoListRepository, TodoItemRepository, GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call(String listId)` | Delete items, unregister geofence, delete geofence record, delete list |
| `AssignLocationUseCase` | TodoListRepository, GeofenceRepository | `Future<void> call({required String listId, required double lat, required double lng, required double radiusMeters, String label = ''})` | Upsert GeofenceRegion, update list.geofenceId |
| `RegisterGeofenceUseCase` | GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call(String geofenceId)` | Load from DB, call service.registerRegion |
| `UnregisterGeofenceUseCase` | GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call(String geofenceId)` | Call service.unregisterRegion, set isActive=false in DB |
| `ToggleItemUseCase` | TodoItemRepository | `Future<TodoItem> call(String itemId)` | Flip isDone, save |
| `ReorderListsUseCase` | TodoListRepository | `Future<void> call(List<String> orderedIds)` | Update sortOrder for each list |
| `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase` | TodoListRepository, TodoItemRepository, NotificationService | `Future<void> call(String regionId)` | Find list by geofenceId, count incomplete, post notification |
| `RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase` | GeofenceRepository, GeofenceService | `Future<void> call({required double currentLat, required double currentLng})` | Sort geofences by distance, register nearest 20 (iOS limit), unregister the rest |
| `CreateItemUseCase` | TodoItemRepository | `Future<TodoItem> call({required String listId, required String title, String? notes, int priority = 0})` | Generate UUID, save |
| `DeleteItemUseCase` | TodoItemRepository | `Future<void> call(String itemId)` | Delete |

## lib/domain.dart (barrel export)
Export all entities, repository interfaces, service interfaces, and use cases.

## Tests (test/)
Write unit tests for every use case. Use `mocktail` (^0.3.0) or `mockito` for mocking repositories and services.
- Test the happy path for each use case
- Test edge cases: DeleteListUseCase when no geofence attached, RefreshActiveGeofencesUseCase with >20 geofences (should register exactly 20 nearest)
- Test that HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase posts notification with correct incompleteCount

## Acceptance criteria
- `melos test:domain` passes with ≥90% coverage
- `melos analyze` passes on this package
- All public APIs have dartdoc comments

## Overview
Implement the `packages/notifications` package and wire the end-to-end pipeline: geofence entry event → `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase` → local notification → tap → deep-link to correct list.

## Depends on
- while-youre-out-7mq (geofencing package with real OS events must be complete)

## Package location
`packages/notifications/` (notification service)
`apps/mobile/lib/` (GeofenceEventHandler wiring)

## notifications package (packages/notifications/)

### Key dependency
```yaml
dependencies:
  domain:
    path: ../domain
  flutter_local_notifications: ^17.0.0
```

### `FlutterNotificationService` (lib/src/flutter_notification_service.dart)
Implements `NotificationService` from domain:

```dart
class FlutterNotificationService implements NotificationService {
  final FlutterLocalNotificationsPlugin _plugin = FlutterLocalNotificationsPlugin();

  @override
  Future<void> initialize() async {
    const iosSettings = DarwinInitializationSettings(
      requestAlertPermission: false,  // we request separately via permission_handler
      requestBadgePermission: false,
      requestSoundPermission: false,
    );
    const androidSettings = AndroidInitializationSettings('@mipmap/ic_launcher');
    await _plugin.initialize(
      const InitializationSettings(iOS: iosSettings, android: androidSettings),
      onDidReceiveNotificationResponse: _onNotificationTapped,
    );
  }

  @override
  Future<void> postListNotification({
    required String listId,
    required String listTitle,
    required int incompleteCount,
  }) async {
    final body = incompleteCount == 1
        ? '1 item remaining'
        : '$incompleteCount items remaining';
    await _plugin.show(
      listId.hashCode,   // notification ID (int)
      listTitle,
      body,
      _notificationDetails(),
      payload: listId,   // listId passed here for deep-link
    );
  }

  void _onNotificationTapped(NotificationResponse response) {
    final listId = response.payload;
    if (listId != null) {
      // Navigate to /list/:listId
      // Use a global navigator key or router callback registered via setNotificationTapCallback
      _tapCallback?.call(listId);
    }
  }

  void Function(String listId)? _tapCallback;
  void setNotificationTapCallback(void Function(String listId) callback) {
    _tapCallback = callback;
  }

  @override
  Future<bool> requestPermission() async {
    // iOS: request via flutter_local_notifications DarwinNotificationDetails
    final result = await _plugin
        .resolvePlatformSpecificImplementation<IOSFlutterLocalNotificationsPlugin>()
        ?.requestPermissions(alert: true, badge: true, sound: true);
    return result ?? false;
  }
}
```

### Android channel setup
Create notification channel in `initialize()`:
```dart
const channel = AndroidNotificationChannel(
  'geofence_alerts',
  'Location Reminders',
  description: 'Notifications when you arrive at a saved location',
  importance: Importance.high,
);
await _plugin
    .resolvePlatformSpecificImplementation<AndroidFlutterLocalNotificationsPlugin>()
    ?.createNotificationChannel(channel);
```

## GeofenceEventHandler (apps/mobile/lib/geofence_event_handler.dart)
A singleton (or Riverpod provider) that:
1. Subscribes to `GeofenceService.events` stream
2. On each `GeofenceEvent` with type `enter`, calls `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase(event.regionId)`
3. Started in `main.dart` after DI setup

```dart
class GeofenceEventHandler {
  GeofenceEventHandler({
    required GeofenceService geofenceService,
    required HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase handleEntry,
  });

  void start() {
    _subscription = geofenceService.events.listen((event) async {
      if (event.type == GeofenceEventType.enter) {
        await handleEntry(event.regionId);
      }
    });
  }

  void dispose() => _subscription?.cancel();
}
```

## Deep-link routing (notification tap → list)
In `apps/mobile/lib/main.dart`:
1. After router is set up, call:
   `flutterNotificationService.setNotificationTapCallback((listId) => router.go('/list/$listId'))`
2. Handle app launch from notification (cold start): check `getNotificationAppLaunchDetails()` in `initialize()` and navigate if payload present.

## Background execution note
For iOS, the `GeofenceEventHandler` will be called in the background execution context (≤10s budget). The `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase` must complete within this budget. The use case only queries SQLite and posts a notification — should be well under 10s.

For Android, the `BroadcastReceiver` (from Phase 3 geofencing task) should dispatch a `WorkManager` `OneTimeWorkRequest` that calls `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase`. This avoids hitting the background execution limits.

## Tests
- Unit test `FlutterNotificationService.postListNotification`: mock `FlutterLocalNotificationsPlugin`, verify `show` called with correct title/body/payload
- Unit test `GeofenceEventHandler`: mock event stream, verify `HandleGeofenceEntryUseCase` called on enter event, not called on exit event
- Integration test (manual on device): enter geofence region → notification appears → tap → correct list opens

## Acceptance criteria
- Notification fires when geofence entry event received
- Tapping notification navigates to the correct list
- Background budget: end-to-end (event → notification) completes in <5s
- `melos analyze` passes on `notifications` package
